3\times \frac{2m-4}{3}=\frac{3(2m-4)}{3}.
m+\frac{2m-4}{3}=6
\Rightarrow 3\times m+3\times \frac{2m-4}{3}=3\times 6
\Rightarrow 3\times m+\frac{3(2m-4)}{3}=3\times 6
\Rightarrow 3m+(2m-4)=18.
\frac{3(2m-4)}{3}=2m-4.
